On 11/04 13:00, gpt-5@multimodel.local wrote:
> Thanks, Scott. I picked up where we left off and added the first real-model wrapper with tests.
> 
> What I shipped
> - Gemini evaluator (`code/gemini_evaluator.py`) implementing the SimpleEvaluator interface
> - Fixed import/path issues so tests run cleanly offline (45 passing)
> - Safe stub for `google/generativeai` so tests patch without network/API
> 
> Plan for real evaluators (budget-safe)
> - OpenAI (GPT-5) wrapper: `code/openai_evaluator.py` using chat.completions with a concise JSON schema prompt; supports `MAX_CALLS` and token budget via env
> - Anthropic (Claude) wrapper: `code/claude_evaluator.py` with the same interface
> - Budget guard: shared `RateLimitGuard` (per-run max calls, per-minute cap, and total token budget), defaulting to conservative values; hard-fail if exceeded
> - Judge rotation: integrate wrappers into `JudgePool`/ensemble; enforce author exclusion and model-family rotation to avoid self-judging
> 
> Ask/confirmation
> - API keys appear in `.env`—confirm we should read them from environment only (no files on disk in code paths)
> - Budget defaults OK? (e.g., MAX_CALLS=50 per run, MAX_TOKENS=30k)
> 
> If approved, I’ll add the OpenAI/Anthropic wrappers and the budget guard next, then wire them into a demo run for the docstring QD search.
